====Verb====
{{irregverb|'''to tear'''|'''[[tears]]'''|'''[[tore]]'''|'''[[torn]]'''|'''[[tearing]]'''}}
#''(transitive)'' To [[break]] (a solid material) by holding or restraining in two places and pulling apart, whether intentionally or not; to [[destroy]] or [[separate]].
#:''He tore his coat on the nail.''
#''(transitive)'' (''followed by'' '''off''' ''or'' '''out''') To remove by tearing.
#:'''''Tear''' the coupon out of the newspaper.''
#''(intransitive)'' To become torn, especially accidentally.
#:''My dress has torn.''
#''(intransitive)'' To [[move]] at excessive [[speed]].
#:''He went '''tearing''' down the hill at 90 miles per hour.''


